    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d47c5646_4641442b",
        "filename": "common/config/validation/handler.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 97,
      "author": {
        "id": 1246322
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-28T21:47:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I had a question about this with respect to using config.ValidationRequestMessage.\nThe content field within that struct is *string, which means that when the json body is decoded into the config.ValidationRequestMessage, it will stay a base64-encoded string.\nDoes that mean that I should not base64-decode it here and leave it to Validator.Func to decode it and leave a note in the comments that the string is base64-encoded?",
      "parentUuid": "fda36384_613a1541",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 97,
        "startChar": 53,
        "endLine": 97,
        "endChar": 76
      },
      "revId": "907a4e90ef9c2ae2882739b622a5f3a9a81944f4",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6b4dbfbf_69cf34a7",
        "filename": "common/config/validation/handler.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 97,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-29T01:15:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "nodir has more context, but in light of what you wrote above, \nyou should base64-decode first *here* and pass result of decoding in whatever form is more efficient.\n\nLooking at https://golang.org/pkg/encoding/base64/, it\u0027d probably be bytes.\nBut maybe we can pass io.Reader instead (see  https://golang.org/pkg/encoding/base64/#NewDecoder),\nwhich could be more efficient for parsing longish config files. The downside is that implementations of Validator.Function will have to perform error checking of base64 format decoding on their side (basically, closing the io.Reader).",
      "parentUuid": "d47c5646_4641442b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 97,
        "startChar": 53,
        "endLine": 97,
        "endChar": 76
      },
      "revId": "907a4e90ef9c2ae2882739b622a5f3a9a81944f4",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "49b26d5b_012f6859",
        "filename": "common/config/validation/handler.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 97,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-29T02:11:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i guess most (all?) configs are protobuf based, which means that io.Reader isn\u0027t really useful, because golang\u0027s protobuf package deserializes from buffer only:\n\nhttps://godoc.org/github.com/golang/protobuf/proto#Unmarshal :(",
      "parentUuid": "6b4dbfbf_69cf34a7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 97,
        "startChar": 53,
        "endLine": 97,
        "endChar": 76
      },
      "revId": "907a4e90ef9c2ae2882739b622a5f3a9a81944f4",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d057e2a2_49ad5d94",
        "filename": "common/config/validation/handler.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 97,
      "author": {
        "id": 1246322
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-29T20:02:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Nodir and I talked this morning and we just decided to change the proto file instead so that content is []byte. Then, it already base64 decodes for us in the json decoding.",
      "parentUuid": "49b26d5b_012f6859",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 97,
        "startChar": 53,
